‚ö†Ô∏è If it fails, there may be a port conflict.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Diagnose Port Usage with netstat

netstat -tulnp

Look for any process using port 5003. If it‚Äôs a non-Apache service (e.g., 247/sendemail:ac), you‚Äôll need to kill it:
kill 247

5Ô∏è‚É£ Re-Start Apache HTTPD
Ensure it starts without error.

6Ô∏è‚É£ Configure Apache to Dnsname on Desired IP and Port

Edit Apache config:
